	</text>
	<text id="nav_text" x="312" y="425" width="463" height="" autosize="H" style="PROMPT" visible="false" fx="PROMPT_SHOW" hidefx="PROMPT_HIDE">
		<content translate="true">Click a &lt;B&gt;Lesson&lt;/B&gt; or &lt;B&gt;Activity&lt;/B&gt; to learn more about &lt;B&gt;Why&lt;/B&gt; &lt;B&gt;Imitation Matters&lt;/B&gt;.</content>
	</text>
	<section id="presentation_text" align="" spacing="0" autospace="false" columns="0" exclusive="false" expanded="true">
		<text id="text01" x="25" y="50" width="361" height="" autosize="H" style="DEFAULT" visible="false" fx="TEXT_SHOW" hidefx="TEXT_HIDE">
			<content translate="true">Imitative behavior provides children with the opportunity to practice and master new skills.</content>
		</text>
		<text id="text02" x="25" y="95.2" width="383" height="" autosize="H" style="DEFAULT" visible="false" fx="TEXT_SHOW" hidefx="TEXT_HIDE">
			<content translate="true">Assimilation:&lt;LI&gt;The child sees something new and takes parts of what she saw and reenacts what had been observed as a self-initiated activity.&lt;/LI&gt;</content>
		</text>
		<text id="text03" x="25" y="172" width="366" height="" autosize="H" style="DEFAULT" visible="false" fx="TEXT_SHOW" hidefx="TEXT_HIDE">
			<content translate="true">Accommodation:&lt;LI&gt;The child takes the newly acquired information and uses it to test variations on the theme.&lt;/LI&gt;</content>
		</text>
		<text id="text04" x="25" y="263.6" width="600" height="" autosize="H" style="DEFAULT" visible="false" fx="TEXT_SHOW" hidefx="TEXT_HIDE"/>
		<text id="text05" x="25" y="221" width="346" height="" autosize="H" style="DEFAULT" visible="false" fx="TEXT_SHOW" hidefx="TEXT_HIDE">
			<content translate="true">&lt;LI&gt;This leads to internalized changes and gains of new knowledge.&lt;/LI&gt;</content>
		</text>
		<text id="text06" x="25" y="265" width="380" height="" autosize="H" style="DEFAULT" visible="false" fx="TEXT_SHOW" hidefx="TEXT_HIDE">
			<content translate="true">&lt;B&gt;Key Message:&lt;/B&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Imitation has varying motivations and purposes at each stage of development.&lt;/LI&gt;</content>
		</text>
	</section>
